AchievementOn(STRING achievement)
Marks achievement as completed. See achievements.doc for possible values

ColorOut(INT unk0, STRING color, INT unk1, STRING unk2, STRING unk3)
Color outro. color is in format #rrggbb

BgLoad(STRING buffer, INT unk0, STRING file)
Loads file into background buffer. Full path is expected.

FadeDelete(STRING buffer, INT unk0, STRING unk1, STRING unk2);
Removes fade effect from buffer

DeleteAllSt(INT unk0, STRING unk1);
Removes all st (characters) from scene

ZoomSG(STRING buffer, INT unk0, INT unk1, INT unk2, STRING unk3, STRING unk4, STRING unk5)
Zoomes scene specified by background buffer.

St(STRING buffer, INT unk0, INT unk1, INT unk2, STRING st)
Loads specified st into buffer. File name only expected.

FadeSt(STRING buffer, INT unk0, STRING unk1)
Fades st from specified buffer.

TypeBegin()
Starts typing text from buffer to textbox

TextBoxDelete()
Removes textbox from scene

CreateMovieSG(STRING buffer, INT unk0, INT unk1, INT unk2, STRING unk3, STRING unk4, STRING unk5, STRING file)
Loads movie from file to buffer. Movies reside in dx/ directory. File name (without extension) only expected

MovieWaitSG()
Waits for currently playing movie to end

SeExPlay(STRING buffer, STRING file, INT unk1, INT unk2, STRING unk3)
Plays specified ambient music (se) file. File name (without extension) only expected.

SePlay(STRING buffer, STRING file, INT unk1, INT unk2, STRING unk3)
Seemingly identical to SeExPlay. (Maybe?) plays only once.

AllShake(INT unk0, INT unk1, INT unk2, STRING unk3, STRING unk4)
Shakes whole screen

CreateBGMovieSG(STRING buffer, INT unk0, INT unk1, INT unk2, STRING unk3, STRING unk4, STRING unk5, STRING file)
Similar to CreateMovieSG, except that movie is part of scene background

SoundPlay(STRING file, INT unk0, INT unk1, STRING unk2)
Plays specified background music (bgm) file. File name without extension expected.

TipsOn(STRING tip)
Briefly show a tip on top of screen.

WaitPlayHalfSG(STRING buffer)
Wait untill half of music specified by buffer is played.

CreateColorEX(STRING buffer, INT unk0, STRING color)
Writes color (#rrggbb) to specified (mask) buffer.

DrawTransitionSG(STRING buffer, INT unk0, INT unk1, INT unk2, INT unk3, STRING unk4, STRING file, STRING unk5, STRING unk6)
Draws buffer with mask loaded from file. File is name without extension expected.

macrosys2_RECEIVE_NEW_MAIL()
Receive mail: Plays music and shows on phone.

macrosys2_DISP_RECEIVEBOX()
Opens phone inbox: Plays music and shows on phone.

macrosys2_DISP_RECEIVED_MAIL_DIRECT()
Displays mail in inbox.

macrosys2_SELECT_PhID();
Selects current $LR_TARGET_PhID in phonebook.

macrosys2_PHONE_ADRSUBMENU_CALL()
Go to call submenu (after selecting in phonebook).

macrosys2_PHONE_CALL_EXEC()
Call current $LR_TARGET_PhID (plays music and shows visual).

macrosys2_CANCEL_PHONE_CALL()
Cancels phone call executed with macrosys2_PHONE_CALL_EXEC().

macrosys2_CLOSE_PHONE_WINDOW()
Removes phone.

PosSt(STRING buffer, INT X, INT unk0)
Offsets St specified by buffer X pixels to the right.
